                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-352-off1811 t18280911-352-crimeloc1814"></join>. I saw the prisoner come to the shop on the 4th of July between three and four o'clock in the afternoon; I was in the back yard and saw him pass round the counter with the bowl of silver in his hand - this is it; it had been in the till.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He picked it up off the ground, and he took and hit me; I hit the bowl, and it fell on the counter, and he gave it to his mother. Witness. I took it from his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-352-person1910">
                  JOHN 
                  COLSON
               <interp inst="t18280911-352-person1910" type="surname" value="COLSON"></interp>
